[SN]TITLE[SN]
Essex builder pins hand to roof with nail gun

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A builder has been rescued from the roof of a house after pinning his hand to a wooden rafter with a nail gun.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The man, in his 30s, became stuck at Layer Breton near Colchester, Essex, on Wednesday afternoon.
He was released from his predicament by firefighters and taken to Colchester General Hospital by ambulance.
The owner of the house, on Shatters Road, said the builder was treated for a flesh wound to one finger and he was expected back at work on Thursday.
The East of England Ambulance Service said it was called at 16:30 BST, while Essex Fire Service sent a triple extension ladder to reach the man who was freed using specialist cutting equipment by 17:10.
